[thinking] I’m pondering whether JUnit loads all test classes before running them. It seems like it might load classes during the discovery phase. If a class imports UsingUnsafe, it might not initialize correctly. Our static block, if loaded during discovery, sets a global safe true very early, which could confuse other tests seeing unsafe as disabled. Existing UsingUnsafeTest uses TestableUsingUnsafe, so there's a custom dispatcher involved. Hmm, I need to ensure that setting safe globally doesn’t mess up other tests!
