en committed. I’m weighing whether to remove it, but deleting it would mean losing a test present from the beginning. The final patch wouldn’t include its deletion, so if the user creates a diff against git, the untracked file will still be there. It might be best to leave it as is for now. Also, I need to mention, “Do not use reflection directly in tests” since we have the method signature `java.lang.reflect.AccessibleObject` due to the public API AccessResolver.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering file updates**\\n\\nI need to focus on dynamic coverage aggregation, especially since `forkEvery=1` indicates it will see direct results. That's good! I might need to update the previous file since it shouldn't be isolated. If I'm using the full, current stale build, I can’t run it. Okay, let’s keep things clear and concise while mentioning that I'm not planning on running it for now.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Updated the active-class coverage work for `org.modelmapper:modelmapper:3.2.0`.\n\nChanges made:\n\n- Added/rewrote dedicated test file:\n  - `tests/src/org.modelmapper/modelmapper/3.2.0/src/test/java/org_modelmapper/modelmapper/ClassInjectorInnerUsingUnsafeInnerFactoryTest.java`\n\n- The test now invokes `ClassInjector.UsingUnsafe.Factory` directly in the system-loaded instrumented ModelMapper classes, rather than through an isolated class loader, so coverage can be attributed to the active class.\n\n- It exercises:\n  - `Factory(AccessResolver)` with an unavailable unsafe dispatcher, reaching the `Field#get(...)` call path.\n  - `Factory.resolve(Instrumentation, false)`, reaching the generated resolver instantiation path with `Class#getConstructor(...)` and `Constructor#newInstance(...)`.\n\n- Updated:\n  - `tests/src/org.modelmapper/modelmapper/3.2.0/build.gradle`\n\n  to set:\n\n  ```groovy\n  forkEvery = 1\n  ```\n\n  for JVM tests, ensuring this test gets a fresh JVM where `UsingUnsafe` has not already been initialized by earlier Mo